Package de.rincewind.api.gui.elements

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ElementBrick
    If the user clicks on this element, on the cursor an item will be set.
    ElementButton
    In this element you can add a listener to run an action on clicking on this element. on that click, the ButtonPressEvent will be fired.
    ElementCounter
    With this element you can count
    ElementInfo  
    ElementInput
    In this element, the user can put items in, and pickup items already dropped in the slot.
    ElementItem
    This is no special element.
    ElementList<T>
    With this element you can create a list of entries and you are able to scroll through the entries.
    ElementMap<T>  
    ElementMultiButton
    In this button, you can run multiple action on one button.
    ElementOutput
    This element allows you to output an item into the slot and let the user get it.
    ElementScanner
    The element allows you to scan the item laying in the slot.
    ElementSelector  
    ElementSwitcher<T>
    This element allows the suer to switch through items, added to this element.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ElementList.ListItem<K>
    This is the class, you can add to the ElementList.
    ElementMap.MapItem<K>  
    ElementSwitcher.SwitchItem<S>
    This is the class, you can add to the ElementSwitcher.
